they grew out of World War I

00:26:39.300 --> 00:26:43.900
and offered a new ideology
based on four freedoms;

00:26:43.900 --> 00:26:47.280
the Freedom of Speech,
Freedom of Worship,

00:26:47.280 --> 00:26:51.730
Freedom from Want,
and Freedom from Fear.

00:26:51.730 --> 00:26:55.440
Roosevelt's four freedoms
became a rallying cry

00:26:55.440 --> 00:26:57.450
to guard a public support

00:26:57.450 --> 00:27:00.930
for America's involvement
in World War II.

00:27:00.930 --> 00:27:04.270
They resonated with the
American people as a statement

00:27:04.270 --> 00:27:07.970
of the country's underlying
values and to this day,

00:27:07.970 --> 00:27:12.370
Roosevelt's four freedoms reigns
through as the basic values

00:27:12.370 --> 00:27:18.250
that defines American life and
examples of American acceptualism.

00:27:18.250 --> 00:27:23.230
Indeed this forum, this book
festival here today is a living

00:27:23.230 --> 00:27:28.240
testament to the core
democratic values of free speech.

00:27:28.240 --> 00:27:32.990
In much the same way as Roosevelt's
four freedoms inspired America

00:27:32.990 --> 00:27:37.160
to wake up and realize what was
happening in the world and to act.

00:27:37.160 --> 00:27:40.980
I have identified what I call
the four freedoms of aging

00:27:40.980 --> 00:27:44.940
that will define our new vision
from living and aging America

00:27:44.940 --> 00:27:47.320
and to inspire us to continue

00:27:47.320 --> 00:27:51.700
to disrupt aging making
that vision a reality.

